<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--ChristmasInJune     06-23 0151</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Christmas In June,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Honolulu Get Christmas Serenade On Radio</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Beachgoers soaking up the Hawaiian summer sun
were serenaded by the strains of ``White Christmas'' and ``Jingle
Bell Rock'' on a radio station here.
   KSSK Radio billed Wednesday as a day of yuletide music to remind
listeners that drinking and driving kills.
   ``We've had 41 traffic fatalities so far this year and if we
continue at this rate we'll have 46 more before Christmas,'' said
Suzi Mechler, KSSK director of operations. ``So we're playing them
their Christmas music now.''
   There were 32 traffic fatalities on Honolulu roads at the same
time last year, police said.
   Mechler said the music also was played to give would-be drinken
drivers a desire to live until Christmas and to think before
getting behind the wheel.
   Mechler said the station has celebrated Christmas in June for
the past three or four years.
</TEXT>
