<HEAD>Doorknob Caper Baffles Police</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Doorknobs are back at police headquarters, but
there are no so suspects in the theft of six ornate knobs stolen
last month.
   Police say they are more vigilant about watching the hardware _
and each other.
   So was the doorknob caper an inside job?
   ``We're not sure who did it,'' police spokesman Jim Jordan said.
``Police or no police, it's a work place.''
   Half a dozen metal knobs the color of pewter and embossed with
the city seal were discovered missing about five weeks ago. They
disappeared one night from middle-level floors, where
administrative offices are located in the seven-floor building that
was built in 1924.
   The knobs have since been replaced, some with the same fancy
design, others without. Jordan said he didn't know the knobs'
value, but said it was modest.
