<HEAD>Iran Reports `Hundreds' of Drug Smugglers Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iranian soldiers arrested ``hundreds'' of
drug smugglers and users and seized more than 1,100 pounds of opium
and heroin in a two-day sweep, Tehran Radio reported.
   The station said Revolutionary Guards in Tehran province began
an anti-drug operation on Monday and seozed 1,089 pounds of opium,
66 pounds of opium extract and more than eight pounds of heroin,
said the report.
   The soldiers also got three revolvers and five million riyals
($74,009) in cash. The radio said a ``large number''of drug
smuggling gangs had been ``smashed.''
   Iran's fundamentalist regime has cracked down harshly on drugs
smugglers and users since it came to power in 1979 and outlawed
cultivation of poppy plants.
