<HEAD>Nearly 400 Pounds Of Cocaine Seized In Belgium</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANTWERP, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police and customs agents seized nearly
400 pounds of cocaine worth $52.7 million in the past two days,
officials said Thursday.
   Police said they seized 200 pounds worth $27.7 million early
Wednesday aboard the Algerian freighter Lafayette. They said a
37-year-old Canadian citizen, only identified as Kenneth M., was
arrested.
   Authorities later Wednesday found 169 pounds of cocaine worth
$25 million after the arrest of a Colombian living in the
Netherlands, identified as Victor Torres-Lanos.
   Police said they began chasing two men after spotting them
aboard the Japanese freighter Caribbean Maru. They said the two
fled by car toward the Netherlands but the car crashed into a
truck. Torres-Lanos was arrested but the other man escaped, police
said.
   Police said they found 55 pounds of cocaine in the car, another
68 pounds near the Japanese ship and 46 more pounds aboard the ship.
