<2ND_LINE>AM-Amnesiac Murder,0368</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Amnesiac Charged In R.I. Murder</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW BEDFORD, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An amnesiac whose picture was
published in a newspaper was identified through fingerprints
Thursday _ by police who charged him with a Rhode Island murder.
   The man who called himself Robert C. Anderson was arrested
Wednesday by Newport, R.I., police, who tentatively identified him
as Robert J. Peabody, 49, of Newport.
   Newport Police Lt. Joseph Subin said Thursday that Peabody's
identity was confirmed by fingerprints. Published descriptions of
Anderson and Peabody had suggested some discrepancies.
   At an arraignment Thursday before Bristol County Superior Court
Judge George N. Hurd, Peabody waived extradition and was turned
over to Rhode Island authorities to face a murder charge. A
Massachusetts charge of being a fugitive from justice was dismissed.
   Peabody was wanted in connection with the slaying of William
Capuano, 34, whose bullet-ridden body was found in a bed and
breakfast inn on May 31. A medical examiner said he had been dead
for at least 48 hours.
   The man who called himself Anderson was picked up with razor
cuts on his arm by Bourne Fire Department paramedics on May 30 at
rest stop on a highway between New Bedford and Cape Cod.
   The man was first put in a hospital, then transferred to a
crisis center where he was arrested Wednesday.
   The Standard-Times of New Bedford published a story Saturday
about the man's search for his identity, and the crisis center
began telephoning area authorities for help.
   ``They ran his picture in the paper,'' Subin said. ``I guess the
center was calling around to see if anyone knew him and we said,
`Yes, we want him for murder.'''
   The man calling himself Anderson told The Standard-Times last
week that he was born July 5, 1944 in Fairfield, Calif., putting
his age at 43. Police said Peabody is a lifelong Newport resident.
   The newspaper said Anderson is blond, 6-foot-4 and weighs 190
pounds. According to employment records, Peabody is 6-foot-2, 205
pounds and has blue eyes and brown hair.
   Anderson told The Standard-Times he believed he was a cook by
trade. Police said Peabody worked in Newport restaurants.
