<1ST_LINE>r f BC-EEC-Inflation     06-23 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-EEC-Inflation,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>EEC Inflation Rose 0.2 Percent In Month, 2.8 Percent In Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Inflation in the European Economic
Community rose an average 0.2 percent in May and 2.8 percent over
the past 12 months, the EEC Statistics Office, Eurostat, reported
Thursday.
   In April, the monthly increase had been 0.6 percent and the
12-month rate 2.7 percent. Yearly inflation stood at 2.9 percent a
year ago.
   Since the beginning of the year, inflation was 1.7 percent
against 1.6 percent a year ago.
   The May inflation rate ranged from a drop of 0.1 percent in
Spain to a 1 percent increase in Denmark. The 12-month increase
ranged from 0.8 percent in Holland to 12.5 percent in Greece.
   ``The inflation rate remains at the same level as a year ago,
which is also the case in the United States and Japan,'' Eurostat
said.
</TEXT>
