<1ST_LINE>u f AM-Shoney's     06-23 0199</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Shoney's,0207</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Shareholders Approve Restaurant Chain Restructuring</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shareholders of Shoney's Inc. on Thursday
approved a $730 million recapitalization plan, which management
says will enable the chain of family restaurants to strengthen its
business without expanding.
   Under the plan, which was first announced in March, stockholders
will receive $16 in cash and $4 in securities for each share and
retain ownership of the stock.
   Financing will be provided through a syndicate of banks led by
the Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce. Other syndicate members
include Chase Manhattan Bank, Mellon Bank, Bank of New York, Bank
of Nova Scotia and Sovran Bank.
   With 1987 sales of $700 million, Shoney's operates and
franchises more than 1,500 family-style restaurants in 30 states
and employs about 25,000 people. It is based in Nashville, Tenn.
   Company executives said when the plan was first announced that
it was designed to shift the company's emphasis from growth through
expansion to growth through improved profit margins at existing
locations.
   In a statement after shareholder approval Thursday, the lead
financing bank said in a statement from New York that the
recapitalization would enable Shoney's to ``respond to the maturing
of the family restaurant industry.''
</TEXT>
