<2ND_LINE>AM-NASD Quotations,0190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>NASD Seeks Electronic Bulletin Board for OTC Stock Quotations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The National Association of Securities Dealers
said Thursday it has asked federal regulators for permission to
begin an electronic bulletin board for price quotations of
low-volume, over-the-counter stocks.
   The NASD currently runs an automated quotation system for
high-volume stocks, but lists prices for smaller stocks by paper in
the so-called ``pink sheets.''
   The association told the Securities and Exchange Commission that
the new bulletin board system, which it wants to operate for a
six-month trial, would cover about 7,000 of the 20,000 to 30,000
pink sheet stocks.
   Many of the issues are low-priced, but some, although traded
thinly or held by only a few owners, are high-priced, it said.
   ``The proposed electronic bulletin board will bring new
visibility and orderliness to (a) large and heterogeneous market,''
NASD President Joseph R. Hardiman said in a statement. It is
expected to speed the process of trading the stocks.
   The NASD said it hopes to get SEC approval for a trial run in
time to begin between July and September.
</TEXT>
